title: For Sale:  AR-15 Upper Complete 7.62x39 AR15 7.62 YHM
postcontent:
For sale or trade is a complete YHM/Citadel 7.5" AR-15 upper half in 7.62x39, complete meaning it does have the BCG and charging handle and is ready to go, just attach to any standard AR-15 lower and you are ready to go.  I am including one C-Products mag, these seem to be the best mags for the AR 7.62x39 round, never any issues when using these mags.  This upper will eat any ammo, Russian steel case or whatever, so it is affordable and reliable to shoot.  The receiver looks great, the rail has some marks here and there from use.  Other features included on the upper are, Daniel Defense sights ($140), Troy Claymore muzzle brake ($64), and the handstop($50), might be KAC, but can't remember.  The hand stop is not a pistol grip.  This upper would cost around $850+ to get the same set-up.

If you are considering a SBR or pistol AR-15, this is the caliber to do it in because this round looses much less velocity and energy compared to the .223 /5.56 round in the shorter barrels.  You can check online, but if I recall a 7.62x39 with 7.5" barrel is still moving right around 2,000 fps vs. 2,400 fps out of a 16" barrel, which is only a 20% or so loss.  I believe the 223/556 round loses around 1/3 of the velocity.  NFA rules apply, you can use as a pistol or SBR if you do the tax stamp first.  Sig does make the stabilizer than looks just like a butt stock and is perfectly legal.

$720 cash firm or $640 without the sights.  Might look at really good trade offers. Will ship for $20 more.

On trades, I have everything I need, but of course like anyone there are still a few "wants" I would like to have, I like a bit of everything.  Just let me know exactly what you have and what you want to do, straight trade, trade +/- cash, ammo, silver, etc. and we'll go from there.  

Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  STI Spartan 1911 9mm w/ Premium Extras!!
postcontent:
Here is an excellent condition, one owner STI Spartan 1911 in 9mm.  STI, based in Texas, is well respected maker among 1911 enthusiasts.  

I purchased this new in 2012 and have fired approx. 150 round.  This pistol has always performed 100% for me; it has never failed to feed, eject, or fire.  In addition, it is a highly accurate firearm; I am attaching an example of a target I personally shot with this pistol (5 shot group, standing unsupported, from 10 yards using inexpensive full metal jacket ammo).  Frankly, it is the most accurate 9mm I own (and that's saying a lot).  This 1911 has a fully adjustable target rear sight, a fiber optic front sight, STI hardwood grips, and many premium extras as follows:

- Cylinder & Slide Short Solid Trigger (fitted specifically to this pistol)
- Evolution Gun Works (EGW) Steel Flat Checkered Mainspring Housing
- Wolf 17 lb. Hammer Spring
- Wilson Combat Stainless Checkered Front Strap (new in package; never used)
- Wilson Combat Hex Head Stainless Screws


As you can see, I have replaced some factory parts with high quality, premium aftermarket parts!  This was done out of personal preference; there was nothing wrong with the factory parts.  You will still get the factory trigger, factory mainspring housing, and factory hammer spring (and I can reinstall these in the pistol if you would like prior to sale).  This gun comes with an 8 round stainless steel Metalform 9mm 1911 magazine.  I am also including the factory case and all factory papers (even includes factory case padlock, bushing wrench, manual, and test fire cases).  The pistol has removable grip tape applied to the front strap of the grip.  I can leave this on or take it off; your choice.  The metal is fine underneath; I simply put this on to make the front strap a little "grippier".  

I am selling this not because there is anything wrong with this pistol, but honestly need to free up some cash for other projects.  

ADDED NOTE:  I will take $15 off the price if you do not want the EGW mainspring housing.  If you choose this option, I will reinstall the factory mainspring housing and spring just like it came when new in box.

Terms of sale:
- Face to face transaction in Peoria or Bloomington preferred, but will ship to your FFL for $35 shipping fee.
- IL buyers must be at least 21 years of age and possess a valid IL FOID.
- Cash accepted for payment; USPS money orders accepted if item is shipped.
- Price is as listed.

title: For Sale:  WTH is with some of the gun prices?!?!?!
postcontent:
I just had to throw in my .02 on some of the listings on this site.  I sell here also, and have bought here.  I try to price my items reasonable even ammo which is hard to get.  For instance I have 5 boxes of 380 ammo for $100.  That's just about what it cost when you could find it and before the shortage.  I understand some premium on maye 22LR or MAG but ALL other ammo can be found with some searching the net and at reasonable prices

Firearms are a whole different issue.  Some of these prices are CRAZY.  I mean I see people selling Glocks for $600.  Nothing extra, nothing special.  Just a Glock.  I can walk into any gun shop and buy any model (well maybe not the 42) for $550 or less and people want more then that for a used gun.  Oh, its been shot only 100 rounds.  Um, its still USED!!!  The Glock is used just to make a point, most listings for any gun are the same.  I agree some firearms go up in value, like maybe a limited run of something or a gun that you cant go and buy off the shelf but otherwise, its like a used car.  Worth less then new.  

If some of you people want to sell your items you have to be reasonable or else your wasting your time or most likely will only attract felons who will pay those crazy prices just to be able to have a gun, which is a whole different topic.  Anyways, just had to throw that out there after reading todays listings.  

Carry on
